🔵 OSI Model — 7 Layers

Layer 7 → Application   → HTTP, HTTPS, DNS
Layer 6 → Presentation  → SSL, TLS, Encryption
Layer 5 → Session       → Sessions, Cookies
Layer 4 → Transport     → TCP, UDP, Ports
Layer 3 → Network       → IP Address, Routing
Layer 2 → Data Link     → MAC Address
Layer 1 → Physical      → Cables, Hardware

--------------------------------
🔵 Layer 3 — Network Layer

Layer 3 = IP Address level

Works with
──────────────────────────────
IP Addresses    ✅
Routing         ✅
Packets         ✅

DDoS attacks at Layer 3
──────────────────────────────
IP Flood        → Send millions of IP packets ❌
ICMP Flood      → Ping flood attack ❌
Smurf Attack    → Spoof IP and flood ❌

🔵 Layer 4 — Transport Layer

Layer 4 = TCP/UDP Port level

Works with
──────────────────────────────
TCP             ✅
UDP             ✅
Port Numbers    ✅

DDoS attacks at Layer 4
──────────────────────────────
SYN Flood       → Flood TCP connections ❌
UDP Flood       → Flood UDP packets ❌
Port Scan       → Scan all ports ❌
